title: Grateful Dead Live at Alpine Valley Music Theatre on 1985-06-22
description:
Set 1

Hell In A Bucket-> Sugaree, Walkin' Blues-> Candyman-> It's All Over Now, Althea, Cassidy, Brown Eyed Women, One More Saturday Night

Set 2

Keep On Growing-> Mississippi Half Step-> Lost Sailor-> Saint Of Circumstance-> Drums-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away, E: Brokedown Palace

reviews.review_text:
Nice second set Except for Dear Mr. Fantasy which both Brent and Jerry butcher the lyrics to. Nice to hear a mellow matrix that lets the soundboard take over when it time to listen to the boys.
The Sailor>Saint has quite a bit of Bobby energy and enthusiasm, something we all love. Drums is high energy and i'm sure the crowd was thrilled (i can actually hear that the crowd was thrilled!)

Crowd noise is necessary to give off a proper idea of the crowd's participating excitement, but not to overwhelm the music
Sometimes these "matrix" remasters have too much AUD imho. This one is well balanced.

I would have only given it three stars because of so many better shows this month. (6/15, 6/28, 6/30) 
BUT... since the matrix is well executed (thanks!) and i'm the first to review... four stars!
Good to hear ALPINE!! Nice Mix with the Matrix brings back a lot of great memories of an underated stop.

Best Walking Blues ever! I'm not a huge fan of the song but this one blew me away.  Seriously, if you find a better version, please post it below.

Jerry - "that's alot of people out there. A lot of people"

EEH The only reason I give this one star is because the quality of the recording is stellar.  These were my first two shows as a taper.  It has to rate as almost the worst of the hundreds of shows I have attended.  Jerry is almost nonexistent during the second set.  Really fast Mississippi half step with a 2 second jam before the Beyond the rio grand e o part.  I'm probably being generous here.  Geez, what's the rush?  Will they turn into pumpkins if they linger on the in between to long?  The second set had the definite feeling that they were trying to get it over with without exerting too much musicianship.  Not fade away-ing into the encore.   Boooooooring!  Surprised they could manage to prop Jerry up for the encore.

This place was special Ear candy. I don't care what anyone says or thinks about this show, I had a beautiful board of this show when I began collecting tapes around 1987 or 1988. Jerry is pretty much missing for most of Keep on Growing, beyond that, this is a wonderful set. I have always thought that this is the best Throwning Stones I have ever heard bar none. You need a really powerful system to do it justice. This set has a lot of sound subtleties that can only be heard when it is cranked. Enjoy! Five stars for the Throwing Stones alone.
Powertful I was there...It is impossible to state some 30 years later just what seeing Jerry and the rest of the boys was like. God bless you Jerry!

Better than I remember These shows were better than I recall. I had let my mediocre audience tapes from back in the day lead me to view  these as rather average shows. But having better quality recordings has made me change my opinion. Alpine was a tough place to get good sounding AUD tapes from the pit. The place had a unique sound that was always different depending on the weather.

While these shows certainly have their share of hit and miss moments, I think these two nights stand up quite well against the rest of the tour.

coming around on 85 Sparkling, stunning recording. Lots of meat to dig into performance-wise. Listen to the subtle delay effect on Jerry's vocal for the verses of Stella. Crank it loud and check the depth

good sound and solid Jerry guitarwork in set 1 sweet sounding Chappie Matrix
you should at least check out the sparkling guitar work and solo's in Sugaree, It's All Over Now, Althea

THIS PLACE ROCKS Hitchhike nine hundred miles to get there from Rhode Island to Alpine and back Jerry was beautiful that night ended up sleeping under the stars tripping brain. What a great night beautiful sound
